      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LOVEMETO NZ (7) added to a string of wins and placings when he came from the back row for a 1.8m second to race rival IM BOBBY here last time. Raced parked and proved too good here prior. Draws wide but the recent consistency is hard to knock. IM BOBBY (8) came from this barrier when getting the better of Lovemeto at this circuit and distance two back then stepped up in trip and missed narrowly last week. Race fit fourth up. Big chance. I AM WILMA (1) made it two wins at this venue in a row when drawing this barrier and using the sprint lane to narrowly beat I Am Bobby last week. Drops in distance but usually performs well at it. KEAYANG STUKA (5) returns to the front row and has been solid in two outings here since a fresh win at Bendigo from a similar draw to this. REMUS PHOENIX (6) has placed behind the top two selections in his two outings since winning here. Respect.",
